{
  "id": 5178789386256384,
  "name": "Support width and height as presentation attributes on nested <svg> elements",
  "summary": "This feature supports applying width and height as presentation attributes on nested <svg> elements through both SVG markup and CSS. This dual approach provides even greater flexibility for developers, allowing them to manage and style SVG elements more efficiently within complex designs.\n\nWith this feature the below two html will now have the same output:\n\nWith CSS Properties for nested <svg> element:\n<svg width=\"100px\" height=\"100px\">\n  <svg style=\"width:50px;height:50px;\">\n    <circle cx=\"50px\" cy=\"50px\" r=\"40px\" fill=\"green\" />\n  </svg>\n</svg>\n\nWithout CSS Properties for nested <svg> element:\n<svg width=\"100px\" height=\"100px\">\n  <svg width=\"50px\" height=\"50px\">\n    <circle cx=\"50px\" cy=\"50px\" r=\"40px\" fill=\"green\" />\n  </svg>\n</svg>",
